{{Unreferenced|date=April 2011}} {{Original research|date=April 2011}} {{Politics of Peru}}
[[File:Bandera del Etnocacerismo.png|200px|center|The etnocacerista flag]]
[[Peru]]'s '''Movimiento Etnocacerista''' (aka '''Movimiento Nacionalista Peruano''' or "Peruvian Nationalist Movement") is a group of [[Ethnic nationalism|ethnic nationalists]]. The name ''etnocacerista'' is composed of two parts: the first evokes Peru's [[Ethnicity|ethnic identity]] (specifically, its origins with the [[Quechua people|Quechua]], a [[Native American (Americas)|Native American]] people often identified in the popular imagination with the [[Inca]], a pre-Columbian royal group); the second indicates the group's veneration of 19th century [[President of Peru|president]] and war hero [[Andrés Avelino Cáceres]], who led a guerrilla resistance campaign against occupying [[Chile]]an troops during the [[War of the Pacific]].
Most of its members are armed forces veterans of [[Internal conflict in Peru|Peru's internal war]] or the border disputes with [[Ecuador]] in the 1980s and 1990s.{{Citation needed|date=June 2013}}
== See also == * [[Antauro Humala]] * [[Isaac Humala]] * [[Ollanta Humala]] * [[Locumba uprising]] ([[:es:Levantamiento de Locumba|es]]) * [[Peruvian Nationalist Party]]
